../../../../promising-findings.md:11:**The theory:** Time is irreversible determination — the ongoing, physically constrained process by which the indeterminate becomes determinate, as encountered from within.
../../../../promising-findings.md:17:  - One-dimensionality: the Margolus-Levitin bound constrains processing to one sequential thread
../../../../promising-findings.md:166:This fork has specific consequences: it determines whether the "now" is ontologically special or merely a computational frontier, whether the arrow is intrinsic or requires the Past Hypothesis, and it maps directly onto real interpretive divides in quantum mechanics (collapse vs. many-worlds vs. hidden variables). Not a verbal difference — it constrains which physical theories are acceptable.
../../../../promising-findings.md:278:**Honest limits:** The budget is vacuous for all macroscopic systems (R_max ~ 10⁴⁰ for a 1m lab). Operationally constraining only at BH horizons, Planck scale, and ultra-cold ion traps. The QD↔HQEC mapping has known gaps (pointer states, δ-threshold, dynamics). BH constants are "overlooked 5-line calculations" — trivial to derive, but unpublished.
../../../../promising-findings.md:311:1. **Within N=4 SYM:** Exact reformulation. Locality and unitarity emerge exactly from geometry (proved for all n,L,k). No experiment can distinguish them. Verified: 4-point MHV amplitude agrees across three methods to 10⁻¹⁵.
../../../../promising-findings.md:315:   - *EFT-hedron positivity bounds:* Constrains which EFTs can be UV-completed via Hankel matrix inequalities. Verified for QED Euler-Heisenberg (c₂/c₁ = 7/4 exactly).
../../../../promising-findings.md:425:**The result:** The spectral approach to RH — finding a self-adjoint operator whose eigenvalues are the non-trivial zeta zeros — was systematically tested against a 10-point quantitative constraint catalog. Every published operator candidate was scored. Central finding: getting GUE statistics is easy (any complex Hermitian matrix does it), but the zeta zeros have 47% stronger long-range rigidity than generic GUE. This "super-rigidity gap" (Δ₃_sat = 0.155 vs best construction = 0.24) is THE obstacle. Berry's 1985 formula explains it analytically from prime orbit structure, but no matrix construction encodes this correctly.
../../../../promising-findings.md:534:**The result:** The De Giorgi recurrence exponent β = 4/3 in Vasseur's (2007) framework for 3D Navier-Stokes regularity CANNOT be improved. All four steps of the De Giorgi proof chain (energy definition → Sobolev embedding H¹ ↪ L⁶ → parabolic interpolation to L^{10/3} → Chebyshev level-set estimate) are individually tight under NS structural constraints. Eight distinct improvement routes were tested and all closed. The exponent is invariant across analytical tools (CZ, IBP, H¹/BMO duality, CRW commutators).
../../../../promising-findings.md:536:**Primary novel finding — sharpness proof:** The constant vector field u(x) = (c, 0, 0) is divergence-free, lies in H¹(T³), and achieves Chebyshev ratio → 1 as λ → c⁻. This one-line construction proves no NS structural constraint can improve the Chebyshev exponent — the bottleneck step. Combined with the established tightness of all other steps, this completes the proof that β = 4/3 is optimal for the De Giorgi–Vasseur framework. No published paper proves this sharpness; Vasseur (2025 survey, arXiv:2503.02575) confirms no improvement in 18 years but does not prove impossibility.
