../../planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-01.md:7:More seriously, the chain is structurally biased toward confirming its founding premise that only a mechanism-changing reformulation matters. That premise may be right, but the chain does not test it fairly. It bakes that worldview into Step 1, carries it through the anti-conjugation rule, and then treats Tao-insensitivity as a sign of weakness rather than as evidence that the candidate may just be another face of the same problem. So the chain is sharp at detecting cosmetic novelty, but not yet sharp at distinguishing genuinely proof-relevant mechanism change from selective narration.
../../planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-01.md:11:### Step 1 - Freeze the endpoint, baseline criterion, and anti-conjugation rule
../../planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-01.md:17:The anti-conjugation rule is directionally correct but still too rhetorical. Many exact reformulations are neither trivially conjugate nor genuinely new. They sit in the middle ground where the nonlinearity is redistributed but not obviously reduced. The current rule does not say how to classify those cases. That invites after-the-fact judgment rather than a reproducible criterion.
../../planning-runs/run-009/attacks/chain-01.md:71:- It underweights prior-art overlap. There is no dedicated step requiring a map from the chosen candidate to known Navier-Stokes reformulations, known commutator identities, or known pressure/localization decompositions. That omission is dangerous because this entire route lives in an area with a long history of exact-but-nonproductive repackaging.
