../../planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:7:Its real strengths should be preserved: it asks for estimate-level gains, rejects identity-level cosmetics, and is willing to end with a negative memo. Its real weaknesses also need repair: it does not fix the architecture sharply enough, leaves the Tao screen too verbal, treats geometry/tensor effects too much as contamination, and makes the negative endpoint easier to earn than the positive one.
../../planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:17:Still, that limitation is acceptable if the branch is labeled honestly. A cleanup test of the "maybe an exact rewrite helps inside the old architecture" loophole is worth running. What is not acceptable is advertising that cleanup branch as a broad search for the mission's hidden mechanism.
../../planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:23:The attacker is right that exact rewrites of the same quadratic nonlinearity usually collapse back to the same localized costs once projection, commutators, and cutoffs are restored. The refined chain should therefore assume collapse is the baseline outcome unless a sharply identified mechanism defeats it.
../../planning-runs/run-003/refined/chain-01.md:24:This branch is worth running because "maybe an exact rewrite helps" is still a live enough loophole to deserve one disciplined closure attempt. What it should not claim to be is a broad discovery program. Its value is precision: either isolate one real estimate-level gain, or kill a narrow family of false hopes cleanly.
