+# Exploration 001 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  build the bounded Step-2 candidate slate for the active exact-rewrite audit,
+  keeping at most two active families and one reserve under the frozen
+  suitable-weak / LEI + CKN ledger from Step 013.
+
+- What I tried:
+  read the Step-013 ledger freeze;
+  reused the Step-005 exact-rewrite family bound;
+  reused the Step-006 candidate screens;
+  checked whether strain / pressure-Hessian or any fourth family had become
+  repository-native exact-rewrite evidence for this branch.
+
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`
+
+- Frozen slate:
+  `active`: `Lamb-vector / Helmholtz-projected form`
+  with exact package
+  `(u . ∇)u = ∇(|u|^2/2) - u x ω`,
+  `P((u . ∇)u) = -P(u x ω)`.
+  Named route back:
+  pressure / projection re-entry into the same `I_flux[phi]` bundle.
+
+  `active`: `vorticity transport / Biot-Savart form`
+  with exact package
+  `ω`-transport plus `u = BS[ω]`.
+  Named route back:
+  Biot-Savart reinsertion of velocity-side factors inside the same
+  `I_flux[phi]` bundle.
+
+  `reserve`: `divergence / stress form`
+  with exact package
+  `(u . ∇)u = div(u ⊗ u)`.
+
+- Why the reserve was not promoted:
+  under the frozen ledger its only named insertion point is integration by
+  parts back to the same stress-against-`∇phi` burden, so it functions more as
+  a control comparator than as a higher-content audit packet.
+
+- One key takeaway:
+  the honest bounded slate is still the original three-family exact-rewrite
+  shortlist, but the two active slots are best spent on the two packets that
+  force the richest re-entry debt audit:
+  pressure/projection for Lamb-vector and velocity reconstruction for
+  vorticity/Biot-Savart.
+
+- Leads worth pursuing:
+  derive the exact and localized equation packets for the two active families;
+  expose pressure re-entry, CZ/commutator debt, and Biot-Savart debt
+  immediately;
+  test whether either active family still touches the full frozen burden rather
+  than only a surrogate object.
+
+- Unexpected findings:
+  the repository-local record already contains strong Step-006 evidence that
+  all three bounded families are Tao-insufficient on the fixed LEI ledger, so
+  `active` here means `audit-priority` rather than `likely survivor`.
+
+- Computations worth doing later if outside scope:
+  none numerical.
+  The next needed work is symbolic/localized equation derivation for the two
+  active packets.
+
+- Omission memo:
+  strain / pressure-Hessian and related older-branch tensor material were
+  omitted because the current branch never froze them as admissible
+  exact-rewrite-native candidates, and Step 010 already killed that family on
+  its own far-field pressure ledger.
